    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="67"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                            type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d67fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché, London, via
                        Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[U.S.S. <hi rend="smallcaps">“Quincy”, at
                        sea</hi>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-28">28 January
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 706, Personal and Top Secret from the President to the Prime Minister.</p>
                <p>Thank you for your 893<note n="2" xml:id="d67fn2">Not printed. This message dealt
                        with details of plans for the flight from Malta to Yalta.</note> and
                        896.<note n="3" xml:id="d67fn3">Not printed. This message dealt with
                        unfavorable travel conditions from the Crimean airport to Yalta.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The approaches to <gloss target="#t_ARGONAUT1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Argonaut</hi>
                    </gloss> appear to be much more difficult than at first reported. I will have my
                    advance party make recommendations as to how I shall travel after Malta.</p>
                <p>I agree that we must notify U. J. as soon as we can fix our schedule in the light
                    of present information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
